#vim-basics

To enter vim we just have to enter in the terminal `$ vim` and vim will start in
the current directory with a blank 'file'.

To exit vim the simplest way is to press `:q` and it will quit the editor, and
to save it we can use `:w`. Both can be combined to save and quit `:wq`.

